<div class="container">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-2">
			<%= select_tag(:company_selector, options_from_collection_for_select(Company.all.order(:name => :asc), :id, :name)) %>
		</div>
		<div class="col-sm-10"> 
			<h1>Stock Talk</h1>
			<h3>Can twitter mentions predict share price?</h3>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-4">
			<ul>
				<li>Zoom in: click & drag</li>
				<li>Zoom out: double-click</li>
				<li>Pan: hold &lt;shift&gt; & drag</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div id="tweetContainer" class="col-sm-8">
			<div id="tweetChart"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-4">
			<div id="finePrint">
				<p>Twitter data are updated at approximately 12:00a, UTC.</p>
				<p>Market data are updated at approximately 2:00a, UTC.</p>
				<p>Gaps in market chart indicate weekends and holidays.</p>
				<p>Gaps in Twitter chart indicate missing data.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div id="priceContainer" class="col-sm-8">
			<div id="priceChart"></div>	
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


